<h1 class="cd-text cd-title">icons</h1>
<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Icon usage</h2>
<ul class="cd-text">
    <li><strong>We use <a href="https://fortawesome.github.io/Font-Awesome/icons/">font awesome icons</a></strong> although please note that not all of the font awesome icons are available in pistachio, only the ones we commonly use.</li>
    <li><strong>Our icons are svgs</strong> because this gives us better performance compared to using an icon font.
    <li><strong>Icons should use the <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element</strong> which covers most, if not all, use cases and is semantically appropriate.</li>
    <li><strong>Icons should use the <code>aria-hidden="true"</code> property</strong> because icons do not really convey any meaning to assistive devices.</li>
    <li><strong>Avoid using an icon on it's own</strong> without providing some visible text that explains the meaning or context. At the very least you should provide some <a href="utilities#accessibility-utilities">text for assistive devices</a>.</li>
</ul>

