<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Icon size</h2>
<p class="cd-text">Icons are sized with <code>em</code> so will typically be the same height as the text in their containing element. Larger icons are suitable for when an icon is <a href="#icons-on-their-own">used on it's own</a> and can be created by using the <code>.fa-2x</code> class.</p>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xxs-6">
        <p>base size</p>
        <span class="fa fa-close" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xxs-6">
        <p>2x size (<code>.fa-2x</code>)</p>
        <span class="fa fa-2x fa-close" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    </div>
</div>

<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Icon colour</h2>
<p class="cd-text">Icons are svgs so will not inherit the colour of their parent element's text. However, every icon has an inverse variant which is used by appending <code>--inverse</code> to the <a href="#icon-library">icon class name</a> and are suitable for use on a dark background, or in coloured buttons.</p>

<div class="page-section page-section--brand page-section--xs">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12 page-section__content text-center">
            <button class="button button--primary"><span class="fa fa-user--inverse"></span> my account</button>
            {{{ getFile 'site/docs/views/examples/icons-inverse.html' }}}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">Icon library</h2>
<div class="row">
{{#each icons}}
<div class="col-sm-6">
    <p><span class="fa {{ name }}"></span> <code>.{{ name }}</code></p>
</div>
{{/each}}
</div>

